messages.text: Brooke?
Are you still there?
Ethan!
You've been texting me in Latin.
What's going on?!
I don't know.
It's all kinda fuzzy.
I saw the dolls again, and my nose is bleeding.
Why do I have a bunch of missed calls from my dad?
I had to.
I'm sorry, babe.
What are you talking about?
What did you do?!
I told him you needed help.
He's coming home to check on you.
Are you SHITTING me?!
Ethan, please!
I'm worried about you.
Your dad found out some stuff about the diary.
What stuff?
Itâ€™d better be good.
Della Dossett was hanged by a lynch mob for the murder of Theodore Tate.
They thought she was a witch because Tate had the same symbol carved on his chest.
Holy shit.
This is messed up.
You know what?
I'm outta here.
Ethan, no!
I gotta go somewhere I can call Quentin Finch in private.
Away from my dad.
Why?
Quentinâ€™s husband has a subscription service to one of those genealogy websites or whatever.
How would that help you?
What are you planning to do?
I gotta find a living Dossett.
Iâ€™m gonna to talk to the witch's family myself.
3 hours and 2 minutes later.
Is this Arianna Dossett?
Who wants to know?
Ethan Owens.
I got your name from a friend of mine.
He found a diary in his attic that was written by one of your ancestors.
So?
So, I need your help.
Are you Arianna Dossett or not?
Yeah. I'm Arianna.
What do you want?
I want to know more about the woman who wrote the diary.
Her name is Della Dossett. She was born in 1793.
Have you heard of her?
Hello?
We've all heard of Della.
You have? How?
My grandmother said she was a witch.
She heard about Della from her Great Aunt Nelly, who heard from her Uncle George, and so on.
It's our family's scary story.
It goes all the way back to Daniel Dossett.
Who's Daniel Dossett?
He was Della's uncle.
After her mother killed herself, he took Della in.
He was 38 when she was hanged.
He told her story to his children, who told their children, et cetera.
What happened back then?
Why did Della murder that Theodore Tate guy?
That "Theodore Tate guy" was Della's dad, but he refused to marry her momâ€”even when she got pregnant.
He was a banker, so he had the money to do itâ€”but he thought Clara Dossett was beneath him.
Whoa.
Yeah. Clara was devastated, and she was seen as a slut after that since she was an unwed mother.
She told her brother Daniel about it, but otherwise, Tate kept the whole affair a secret.
Total jerk.
He did send stuff to Della, thoughâ€”to keep Clara quiet.
He bought her silence?
Yeah. He secretly sent her baby clothes, blankets, and a whole lotta dolls.
DOLLS?!
Yeah, like porcelain dolls.
What happened to them?
Well, Tate had stuff delivered to Della but he refused to talk to her mom, like, at all.
Clara was totally heartbroken the whole time, and I guess she cracked for good when Della was 3.
Cracked?
She went nuts and thought the dolls were watching her or something.
She poked out their eyes with an ice pick and threw herself into the Hudson.
WHOA.
That's when Della went off to live with her Uncle Daniel.
And then she became a witch?
Well, according to the story, she was a pretty creepy child.
How so?
My family says she had a fit when Daniel tried to get rid of the broken dolls.
He eventually let her keep them, but she never touched them again.
They ended up full of cobwebs.
She also rarely spokeâ€¦
And she drew weird symbols everywhere, even on her bedroom walls.
Stuff like that.
And what about Tate?
After Clara died, he stopped sending dolls to Della.
He forgot about her, and no one outside the family knew he was her dad.
But she never forgot about him.
She waited until she was 15 and then she tracked him down.
And carved a symbol on his chest to get revenge?
How does a 15-year-old girl get the better of a fully-grown man?
She seduced him.
OMG, ew.
Seriously, she seduced her own father?!
Well, he didn't know she was his daughter.
He'd never actually seen her before.
She flirted her way into his house, knowing he had a bad habit of sleeping with young girls.
And before he had the chance to touch her, she drugged his drink.
How would anyone know that?
Did she confess?
Her Uncle Daniel had a son, Duke.
He was about Della's age, and she confided in him.
She told him all the stuff she did.
Which was what, exactly?
She cursed Theodore Tate, carving that the symbol in his flesh to control his mind.
She totally tortured him.
How?
She gave him nosebleedsâ€¦
Convulsions that looked like seizuresâ€¦
And hallucinations about the terrible dolls he'd given her.
Holy shit.
The night Tate died, she met him by the river and told him she was his daughter.
She asked him why he'd forgotten about her.
And how did he answer?
He just shrugged, like it didn't matter to him one bit.
So she said, "I'll make you remember me."
In Latin?
Yeah, and she walked away.
But then she turned back, looked Tate directly in the eyes, and willed him into the river.
And they were in the exact same spot where, 12 year earlierâ€¦
Her mother had thrown herself in.
